radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated and fluid filled measuring 11 mm in diameter with hyperemic mucosa and surrounding stranding. No extraluminal air is seen. There is a small amount of fluid measuring 1.7 x 0.7 cm adjacent to the appendix. The bases of the lungs are essentially clear bilaterally. The liver is homogeneous with no focal lesion identified. No intrahepatic biliary dilatation. The pancreas, spleen, and bilateral adrenal glands are within normal limits. The kidneys present symmetric nephrograms and excretion of contrast. No hydronephrosis or perinephric stranding.
